  "prompt": "Who and where were we before we were born?",
  "response": "This is a profound philosophical and existential question that different belief systems and cultures answer in various ways:\n\n1. Scientific perspective:\n- Before birth, we did not exist as individual conscious beings\n- We were potential genetic material from our parents\n- Our physical components existed as atoms in the universe\n\n2. Religious perspectives:\n- Hinduism/Buddhism: Believe in reincarnation, suggesting souls exist and cycle through different lives\n- Christianity/Islam: Generally believe souls are created by God at conception\n- Some traditions suggest souls exist in a spiritual realm before physical birth\n\n3. Philosophical perspectives:\n- Some philosophers argue consciousness emerges from physical brain processes\n- Others suggest consciousness might be a fundamental aspect of universe\n- Plato's theory of forms suggests souls exist in an ideal realm before physical life\n\n4. Metaphysical views:\n- Some believe in a pre-existence state of consciousness\n- Others see humans as part of a larger universal energy or consciousness\n\n5. Personal interpretation:\n- Ultimately, this remains a deeply personal and subjective question\n- Different individuals find meaning through scientific, spiritual, or philosophical lenses\n\nNo definitive, universally accepted answer exists. What resonates depends on individual beliefs, cultural background, and personal understanding.\n\nWould you like to explore any of these perspectives in more depth?",
